				\begin{document}$${C}_{min}={C}_{0}.{t}^{-k}$$\end{document}Cmin=C0.t−kwhere, Cmin is SOC mineralization rate, C0 is the labile pool SOC (mg C kg−1), k is the decomposition rate constant (day−1), and t is the decomposition time in days. The model parameters were estimated by pooling the observed SOC mineralization data over three replications. Model performance under each treatment variable was compared using Pearson’s correlation coefficient (r) between the observed and predicted values, RMSE, and NRMSE. The RMSE was estimated as a mean squared error between the model-predicted values and the observed values, and NRMSE as a RMSE value standardized with the means of the observed values21. A good model fit has a greater r value and lower RMSE and NRMSE.
